After solving all of the puzzles (so far) in the CrossMe Premium, I had to buy the CrossMe Color app. Like the original, I find the puzzles challenging but not so difficult that they can't be solved (particularly as you move up the difficulty scale). The color definitely makes more visually appealing pictures afterwards, and makes it both more complex and easier to handle.  If I have one complaint, it is that there is no way to mark squares as not having a specific color. With the original, there were three "settings", colored, "X-ed" (which indicated that the square should remain blank) and empty (which, for me, indicated that the square was as-yet unknown). With Color, different colored squares can be right next to each other. I have to be very careful about marking X, because that means the box is supposed to be empty of all colors. That can make it difficult to manage multiple colors on a large puzzle (I have a 4" screen on my phone, it might be different if I were using a tablet). I would prefer a way to say "Red doesn't go here, but blue or green may." Not sure how to do that, though.

Reading phone status is necessary to shut off for phone calls, not sure why people want to be so paranoid.

Love the game at least as much as the original version. It should be pointed out that this doesn't "just"  add color... it adds complexity too! Whereas in the black only version you ALWAYS have an empty boxe(s) between runs of squares, you now ONLY have a blank space guaranteed IF two sequential runs off squares are of the same color. Runs of different colors CAN be side by side. This may not sound like much but it complicates solving methods in the harder puzzles... which makes it all the more fun!

I love, love, love the game. The original had me playing non stop. I actually paid for an app and felt compelled to leave a review, which I have never done. But the newest update needing to read my phone status and incoming phone calls is suspicious and ridiculous. If I had a phone instead of tablet I wouldn't have installed.  buyer beware.
awesome game but puzzle 4.13 doesnt work properly for me

Loved this game in the original.  Even better in color.  Definitely worth the money.  Much better than the new craze of games that ask you constantly spend cash to buy every little thing within the game.
